Package edu.sjsu.group_assignment

Class AppointmentManager

java.lang.Object
edu.sjsu.group_assignment.AppointmentManager
public class AppointmentManager extends Object
AppointmentManager class manages a collection of appointments by using TreeMap where the key is a description String and value is an Appointment object.
Author:
Lilou Sicard-Noel, Yipeng Liu, Zhuying Wang
See Also:
TreeMap

    • printAppointment

      public String printAppointment​(Comparator<Appointment> compare)
      Print all appointment in the treemap in there natural order or an error message if the treemap is empty This use a comparator to sort the printed item. The sortage can be by Start Date or Description. Remember that an appointment's description is unique. Right now, compare to return the comparison of the description
      Parameters:
      compare - The comparator object

    • saveToFile

      public boolean saveToFile​(String outputFile, Comparator<Appointment> comparator, boolean isAppending)
      A method to save the appointments to a file. Each line includes the information of one appointment.
      Parameters:
      outputFile - A String for the output file path.
      comparator - An Appointment Comparator.
      isAppending - A boolean flag for appending check: true for appending, false for not.
      Returns:

    • saveToFile

      public boolean saveToFile​(String outputFile)
      A method to save the appointments to a file. Each line includes the information of one appointment. Default comparator to null and isAppending to false. In other words, using the natural order and overwriting the save file.
      Parameters:
      outputFile - A String for the output file path.
      Returns:
      A boolean value. True if Appointments have been successfully saved to the output file, or false otherwise.
